I use two D-locks. One at the rear, through the rear triangle &amp; one at the
front through a wheel. If space, I'll also thread a cable lock around &amp;
through bits too. The bottom line is nothing will stop a really determined
thief, but the idea is to make your steed less attractive to an opportunist
thief than the steed next to it... Also - check your insurance policy to see
what is required by way of locking, so that if the worst happens and your
steed is stolen, at least you can claim a replacement on your insurance
policy.
