Hi
I have a recumbent trike for10 years  and have cycled and locked it
hundreds of times in several European countries.
I always try to lock it where it is overlooked.
For day locking I use a multi strand 1 metre strop 3/8 diameter
plastic covered- locked with a circular standard lock costing £10
Overnight I cover it with a grubby builders polythene purpose made
cover- seams are held together with duct tape.
I add a Kryptonite u lock to lock the back wheel.
I use &quot;unattractive&quot; components-eg hub brakes-Shimano mid range rings
gears-20&quot;wheels Sachs 7x3 hub.
I do not take it to locations where there are expert bike thieves-eg
Amsterdam and sadly- France-because my rusty upright-which had no
value-was cut from the back of my car in Arras of all places.
Its just a question of common sense-and-luck- where I lock my bike in
Berlin my friend has had two bikes stolen in 4 years-but-she leaves
them locked in the same place all summer.
One year I lost my lock key and cut through the 3/8 strop in 5 minutes
using a junior hack saw-it was broad daylight in a busy street-the
only people interested were the Berlin bin men-who offered lots of
practical-and unprintable advice.
Tam

